cast.overview: After a bleak childhood, Jane Eyre goes out into the world to become a governess. As she lives happily in her new position at Thornfield Hall, she meet the dark, cold, and abrupt master of the house, Mr. Rochester. Jane and her employer grow close in friendship and she soon finds herself falling in love with him. Happiness seems to have found Jane at last, but could Mr. Rochester's terrible secret be about to destroy it forever?
cast.title: Jane Eyre

details.biography:
Based in SE London, Sally began acting in childhood, from school plays all the way to the National Youth Theatre. She trained in Live Art at De Montfort University and then set up her own theatre company - Gin Theatre in 1992. Gin Theatre specialised in new writing and toured nationally in the early 90s.

Television, commercial and film work followed including The Basil Brush Show, Maybe Baby, Bright Star, Jane Eyre, Killing Eve and many others. Sally made her West End debut in English National Opera’s production of Cosi Fan Tutti directed by Phelim McDermott for Improbable.

Sally is also a local celebrity amongst Lewisham toddlers due to her preschool music classes Singalong Sally . After raising two neurodiverse sons, Sally is an active campaigner for families affected by Autism.
details.name: Sally Reeve
